Nit: I don't think that we need this new method on the `Decrypter` interface. Instead, we could let this live on a separate interface and polyfill it for `Decrypter`s that don't implement it. Something like:

```go
type BulkDecrypter interface {
	BulkDecrypt(ciphertexts []string) (map[string]string, error)
}

func BulkDecrypt(dec Decrypter, ciphertexts []string) (map[string]string, error) {
	if bulk, ok := dec.(BulkDecrypter); ok {
		return bulk.BulkDecrypt(ciphertexts)
	}

	result := make(map[string]string, len(ciphertexts))
 	for _, c := range ciphertexts {
		plaintext, err := dec.DecryptValue(c)
		if err != nil {
			return nil, err
		}
		result[c] = plaintext
 	}
 	return result, nil
}
```

That way, not every `Decrypter` has to implement `BulkDecrypt`--only those for which it provides meaningful additional value.

